8383,"WN439","Programming","Jochen Topf released the Osmium library 2.15.0, the Python bindings for Osmium PyOsmium, 2.15.0, the Osmium command line tool 1.10.0, and the OSMCoastline 2.2.1 program recently. The new Osmium library uses a lot less memory, with savings up to 50 percent. PyOsmium now uses PyBind11 internally to connect the C++ Osmium library instead of building on Boost as before. Jochen [explains](https://blog.jochentopf.com/2018-12-11-osmium-releases.html) further enhancements on his blog.",4

16353,"WN628","OSM in action","New instructions for setting up a rendering server on Ubuntu 22.04 were [published](https://switch2osm.org/serving-tiles/manually-building-a-tile-server-ubuntu-22-04-lts/)  when that version of Ubuntu was released. In a diary entry, SomeoneElse [explained](https://www.openstreetmap.org/user/SomeoneElse/diary/399648) that setting up replication with `osm2pgsql` or `PyOsmium` and monitoring with `munin` is much easier now, as Ubuntu provides up to date packages for `osm2pgsql` and `osmium`, so that a manual build from source is not needed any more.",4

17106,"WN650","Programming","[RGCosm](https://github.com/punnerud/rgcosm) is a new minimal 'Reverse Geocode for OpenStreetMap'. According to the developer's _Hacker News_ [announcement](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34191433): '[ChatGPT](https://openai.com/blog/chatgpt/) wrote most of the code for me. Created it in about three hours, where the time is combined with creating the DB, and testing it with the rest of the code for a different project' (sqlite3 + python + [pyosmium](https://github.com/osmcode/pyosmium)).",4

19987,"WN726","Programming","Bulgent [provided](https://qiita.com/Bulgent/items/518a3bfa08eb9bdef476) :JA-s: >   [:EN-t:](https://qiita-com.translate.goog/Bulgent/items/518a3bfa08eb9bdef476?_x_tr_sl=auto&_x_tr_tl=EN) an introduction to using PyOsmium, a Python library for processing OpenStreetMap data. The post covers installation, basic usage, data extraction, geographic calculations, and GeoJSON output. He also contrasts PyOsmium with another library, Pyrosm, highlighting their respective strengths and weaknesses for different OSM data processing tasks.",4

20623,"WN740","Releases","Sarah Hoffmann [announced](https://www.openstreetmap.org/user/lonvia/diary/405152) the release of version 4 of pyosmium, a Python wrapper for the Osmium C++ library, used for reading, writing, and processing OSM data. This major update includes several new features, such as iterative processing, filter functions, and an OSM data writer with automatic reference completion.",4

21438,"WN760","Programming","Sarah Hoffmann has been [selected](https://nominatim.org/2025/02/06/sovereign-tech-fellowship.html) for the one-year pilot of the [Sovereign Tech Fellowship](https://www.sovereign.tech/news/meet-the-sovereign-tech-fellows

) programme by the Sovereign Tech Agency. The fellowship will provide support for the maintenance of Nominatim, Photon, [osm2pgsql](https://osm2pgsql.org/news/2025/02/06/sovereign-tech-fellowship.html), and pyosmium throughout the next year. Congratulations Sarah!",4
